    '{"A":"It is less suitable for manufacturing large volumes of planar p-i-n perovskite solar cells than an alternative fabrication","B":"It is more expensive when manufacturing at scale than are processes for fabricating ETLs used in other perovskite solar","C":"It typically entails a greater loss of nanoparticle solution than do other established approaches for ETL fabrication.","D":"It is somewhat imprecise and therefore limits the potential effectiveness of p-i-n planar perovskite solar cells at capturing"}',
